<paragraph id="A928076B6AD1CCFF99938015976A5966" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218">
<taxonomicName id="6BE08C8AFA97D18B410A158ED123693D" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophilidae" genus="Boletina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Boletina pallidula" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidula">Boletina pallidula</taxonomicName>
Edwards, 1925: 573 (
<bibRefCitation id="9CDF314B78A8119B46E5863899E38005" author="Edwards, F. W." journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" pagination="505 - 670" title="British fungus-gnats (Diptera, Mycetophilidae). With a revised generic classiﬁcation of the family." volume="1925" year="1925">Edwards 1925</bibRefCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="92A730626A666323FB82DBDFAF4018D5" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218">
<taxonomicName id="E84976F946D7B0BFA548D2038A774F4E" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophilidae" genus="Boletina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Boletina subnitidula" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subnitidula">Boletina subnitidula</taxonomicName>
Sasakawa, 1994: 298 (
<bibRefCitation id="AE0E2F054F0DBE3BB22ED15A75113499" author="Sasakawa, M." journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Shikoku Entomological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" pagination="293 - 306" title="Fungus gnats associated with flowers of the genus Arisaema (Araceae). Part 2. Keroplatidae and Mycetophilidae (Diptera)" volume="20" year="1994">Sasakawa 1994</bibRefCitation>
), syn. n.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B7299FF4CBAFD6B9C96933E0A619C63F" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph id="8ED163E83CB3664D5A3BDE4457376165" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AC2E4E17E0ADD2D835D4C4A59EB69172" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218">
<taxonomicName id="6639637E2D07F225A55CF21FED129AE8" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophilidae" genus="Boletina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Boletina pallidula" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidula">Boletina pallidula</taxonomicName>
was described by Edwards (
<bibRefCitation id="B138696D61F32EFBB0CF233059003CCF" author="Edwards, F. W." journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" pagination="505 - 670" title="British fungus-gnats (Diptera, Mycetophilidae). With a revised generic classiﬁcation of the family." volume="1925" year="1925">Edwards 1925</bibRefCitation>
) from the British Isles, and the male hypopygium has been later illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="1FF8BB989CEB878804306F702287845C" author="Hutson, AM." journalOrPublisher="Handbooks for Identification of British Insects" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" title="Mycetophilidae (Bolitophilinae, Ditiomyiinae, Diadocidiinae, Keroplatinae, Sciophilinae and Manotinae). Diptera, Nematocera" year="1980">Hutson et al. 1980</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="96C87E180916C5230858ECB339032535" author="Zaitzev, A. I." journalOrPublisher="Nauka, Moscow" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" title="Fungus gnats of the fauna of Russia and adjacent regions. Part 1." year="1994">Zaitzev 1994</bibRefCitation>
. The species has a European range, including Fennoscandia, northern Russia, Central Europe, Bulgaria and Hungary (
<bibRefCitation id="2E09628F25B59212B31D9833498FC6E4" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218">Chandler 2014</bibRefCitation>
). Sasakawa (
<bibRefCitation id="8C52C7C90A635B3BB627EAEF73DB7695" author="Sasakawa, M." journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Shikoku Entomological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" pagination="293 - 306" title="Fungus gnats associated with flowers of the genus Arisaema (Araceae). Part 2. Keroplatidae and Mycetophilidae (Diptera)" volume="20" year="1994">Sasakawa 1994</bibRefCitation>
) described 
<taxonomicName id="BA0657179CB3539711E276F59ABB7F07" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Biddulphiaceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="B. subnitidula" order="Biddulphiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="subnitidula">B. subnitidula</taxonomicName>
from the Chiba prefekture in Japan based on material collected from 
<taxonomicName id="B05BA373B5D0A95C3512DA184A2A5254" genus="Arisema" lsidName="Arisema serratum" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" rank="species" species="serratum">Arisema serratum</taxonomicName>
flowers. Sasakawa's description is very detailed, including illustrations on the male hypopygium, and hence we propose it as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="CB2F7744CD129D51EC812731C5F96C03" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Biddulphiaceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="B. pallidula" order="Biddulphiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="pallidula">B. pallidula</taxonomicName>
. In his discussion on 
<taxonomicName id="AA9AB91398950B4E783BA70187A854D2" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Biddulphiaceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="B. subnitidula" order="Biddulphiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="subnitidula">B. subnitidula</taxonomicName>
Sasakawa (
<bibRefCitation id="286079CC81E524AD2FACB581A1640162" author="Sasakawa, M." journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Shikoku Entomological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" pagination="293 - 306" title="Fungus gnats associated with flowers of the genus Arisaema (Araceae). Part 2. Keroplatidae and Mycetophilidae (Diptera)" volume="20" year="1994">Sasakawa 1994</bibRefCitation>
, p. 300) does not mention 
<taxonomicName id="3A3C384968FE17C9EE5EE35266E36540" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Biddulphiaceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="B. pallidula" order="Biddulphiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="pallidula">B. pallidula</taxonomicName>
; instead, he compares his new species to rather distant species 
<taxonomicName id="5D188E29B41EFCA24238A414B5CDD4D8" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Biddulphiaceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="B. nitida" order="Biddulphiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="nitida">B. nitida</taxonomicName>
Grzegorzek and 
<taxonomicName id="120DDA884A9845305D46B93FC964DB1A" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Biddulphiaceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="B. dispecta" order="Biddulphiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="dispecta">B. dispecta</taxonomicName>
Dziedzicki. It is likely that Sasakawa was not aware of 
<taxonomicName id="AD25FFBC50ADBB560AB27E0955986249" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Biddulphiaceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="B. pallidula" order="Biddulphiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="pallidula">B. pallidula</taxonomicName>
while describing 
<taxonomicName id="B0D92C601F28578D0E808BC2EDE6F0BD" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Biddulphiaceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="B. subnitidula" order="Biddulphiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="subnitidula">B. subnitidula</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
